  "text": "Baselines. There are no direct baselines to our approach since the problem de nition is novel. Instead we focus on comparing our method with the two techniques that inspired our approach. The rst method is by Sintos and Tsaparas [CITATION_1] and it maximizes the number of strong edges while keeping the number of violations equal to 0. The second method is by Angluin et al. [CITATION_2] and it minimizes the number of edges needed to connect the communities. We refer to these methods as Sintos and Angluin, respectively, and we call our method Greedy.",
